   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Tutorial with Qiskit\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates several examples of generating Quantum Convolutional Neural Networks (QCNNs) using the package. Default circuits/ansatzes for convolution and pooling operations are shown, such as the CRZ gate for convolutions and CNOT for pooling, to facilitate an easy visual representation of the package's functionality. The section [custom unitaries](#sec_customunitary) illustrates how to specify custom unitaries for convolutions, pooling, or other primitives.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Important**\n",
    "Qiskit requires QASM valid qubit names, such as \"q1\", \"q2\" and won't accept pure ints to reference qubits. For this reason when specifying qubits with `Qfree()`, if you provide ints, they will be prepended with a \"q\". i.e.\n",
    "`Qfree(3) -> [\"q1\", \"q2\", \"q3\"]`\n",
    "\n",
    "`Qfree([5,6,9]) -> [\"q5\", \"q6\", \"q9\"]`\n",
    "\n",
    "`Qfree([\"qubit_1\",\"qubit_2\",\"qubit_3\"]) -> [\"qubit_1\",\"qubit_2\",\"qubit_3\"]`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1669c9a9-9853-49f3-86ca-765242d0670c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___\n",
    "*A cute robot building itself with artifical intelligence, pencil drawing -  generated with* [Dall E 2](https://openai.com/dall-e-2/)\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"../img/DALLÂ·E 2022-08-17 11.48.32 - A cute robot building itself with artifical intelligence, pencil drawing.png\" alt=\"drawing\" width=\"200\"/>"
   ]

    "# Core library functionality\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qcnn, Qfree, Qconv, Qpool, Qdense, plot_motif, plot_motifs"

    "# Specific to Qiskit\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import Parameter, QuantumCircuit, QuantumRegister\n",
    "from hierarqcal.qiskit import convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "82f7ea3d-564f-4edc-90f6-6240f0bd600a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Basic example\n",
    "We create one of the architectures discussed in [Lourens et al.](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2210.15073.pdf). This architecture is semantically described as repeating a convolution of stride 1 and pooling from bottom to top on 8 qubits until one remain.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"../img/hierarchical_motifs.drawio.svg\" alt=\"hierarchical motifs\" width=\"900\"/>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "8a2b1b8e-b7c9-45d5-969c-bd8d5f7efa59",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2210.55x702.333 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "m = Qfree(8) + (Qconv(1) + Qpool(filter=\"right\")) * 3\n",
    "\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(m)\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f75603b0-0221-43a3-9f42-d3b508f355fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Building blocks\n",
    "Circuit architectures are created by stacking motifs hierarchacially, the lowest level motifs (primitives) are building blocks for higher level ones. On a high level you can regard a primitive as a layer such as convolution or pooling and we're creating a sequence of layers for the circuit. This view only captures hierarchical architectures of two levels (*level 1 -> primitives, level 2 -> sequence of primitves*). The framework is more general in that there is no limit to the number of levels used to represent an architecture. See the comparison below:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Layer view**\n",
    " - qcnn = (Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Convolution, Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Pooling)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hierarchical view**\n",
    " - m2_1 = (Convolution, Pooling)\n",
    " - m2_2 = (Convolution, Convolution)\n",
    " - m3_1 = (m2_1, m2_1)\n",
    " - qcnn = (m3_1, m2_2, m3_1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6e3dd676-608d-471f-a788-380753733cbb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Free qubit primitive\n",
    "We first need to specify the qubits for operations to act, this is achieved with the `Qfree` primitive. It is a special motif with no operational effect that makes qubits available and unavailable for succesive operations. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "62eb26d8-7132-4206-8190-4f0c01823470",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Free primitive, can also recieve a list of qubit lables to make available.\n",
    "q8 = [f\"q{i}\" for i in range(1,9,1)]\n",
    "free = Qfree(q8)  # Qfree(8) or Qfree([2,6,4,10]) or Qfree([\"q1\", \"q2\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plot_motif(free)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6429bffb-448a-4811-b8a0-7321773ea662",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Convolution primitive\n",
    "To visualise the convolution operation we free up 8 qubits and add a convolution of stride 5 motif"

   ],
   "source": [
    "### Reverse binary tree\n",
    "\n",
    "# Change these values\n",
    "# ---------\n",
    "N = [f\"q_{i}\" for i in range(1,9,1)]  # any power of two\n",
    "s_c = 1  # 1,2,3, ...\n",
    "f = \"inside\"  # right, left, inside, outside, even, odd\n",
    "s_p = 0  # 1,2,3, ...\n",
    "# ---------\n",
    "\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(stride=s_c)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qpool(stride=s_p, filter=f)\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_1 + m1_2\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + m2_1 * int(np.log2(len(N)))\n",
    "\n",
    "figs = plot_motifs(m3_1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a14f59f6-156f-4490-aa10-1deac3c1f0aa",
   "metadata": {},

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "cc563ad9-b1f1-49a0-ba6c-2a1b198d4035",

   ],
   "source": [
    "m1 = Qfree(6) + Qconv()\n",
    "m2 = m1 + Qpool(1, \"000101\")\n",
    "m3 = m2 + Qfree(8) + Qconv(1) + Qpool(2, \"11111110\")\n",
    "m4 = m3 + Qfree(4) + (Qconv(1) + Qpool(0, \"even\")) * 2\n",
    "m5 = m4 + m4\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(m5)\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\", scale=0.5)"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "b295f146-8fa5-4cd2-847f-db06b79f51f3",

   "outputs": [

     "data": {

     },

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 8\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(2)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qpool(filter=\"left\")\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_1 + m1_2\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + m2_1 * int(np.log2(N))\n",
    "\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(\n",
    "    (m3_1 + Qfree([1, 3, 5]) + Qconv(5) + m3_1) * 4\n",
    ")\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\", scale=0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fd865c61-a965-4a02-9645-3f58841a8341",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Multiscale Entanglement Renormalization Ansatz (MERA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "e7d55491-29fd-490c-9f43-719cd0a6d207",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1792.5x702.333 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "### MERA like\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(1, 2)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qconv(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "m1_3 = Qpool(filter=\"1001\")\n",
    "m1_4 = Qpool(2, filter=\"001001\")\n",
    "m1_5 = Qpool(filter=\"outside\")\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_2 + m1_1\n",
    "m2_2 = m1_3 + m1_4\n",
    "m2_3 = m1_5\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + (m2_1 + m2_2) * 2 + m2_1\n",
    "\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(m3_1)\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb88b1e8-1eeb-445e-9d17-cd1cfc5b59e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Random QCNNs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "1de73952-5198-4784-8c0c-34b44209569f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1876.11x702.333 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 18,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# More structure\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from functools import reduce\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qmotifs\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "M = Qcnn(N)\n",
    "n = len(M.tail.Q_avail)\n",
    "while n > 1:\n",
    "    p = [\n",
    "        Qpool(s_p, filter=i_filter)\n",
    "        for i_filter in (\"right\", \"left\", \"even\", \"odd\", \"inside\", \"outside\")\n",
    "        for s_p in range(n)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    c = [\n",
    "        Qconv(stride=s_c, step=s_t, offset=s_o)\n",
    "        for s_c in range(1, n, 1)\n",
    "        for s_t in range(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "        for s_o in range(n)\n",
    "    ]  # + [Qdense()]\n",
    "    M = M + random.choice(c) + random.choice(p)\n",
    "    n = len(M.head.Q_avail)\n",
    "\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(M)\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "05e3ba8c-5f7c-462c-9990-41b50f4ced68",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1792.5x702.333 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 19,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# loose\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from functools import reduce\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qmotifs\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "M = Qcnn(N)\n",
    "n = len(M.tail.Q_avail)\n",
    "while n > 1:\n",
    "    p = [\n",
    "        Qpool(s_p, filter=i_filter)\n",
    "        for i_filter in (\"right\", \"left\", \"even\", \"odd\", \"inside\", \"outside\")\n",
    "        for s_p in range(n)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    c = [\n",
    "        Qconv(stride=s_c, step=s_t, offset=s_o)\n",
    "        for s_c in range(1, n, 1)\n",
    "        for s_t in range(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "        for s_o in range(n)\n",
    "    ] + [Qdense()]\n",
    "    M = M + random.choice(c) + random.choice(p)\n",
    "    n = len(M.head.Q_avail)\n",
    "\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(M)\n",
    "circuit.draw(\"mpl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bede20f2-cee9-47a1-ad28-6a7fca604625",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "<a id='sec_customunitary'></a>\n",
    "## Specifying custom unitaries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "5a2332df-b595-43be-b5a6-b1c57c466d09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pooling circuit\n",
    "def V(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    # gate operations:\n",
    "    circuit.crz(symbols[0], q0, q1)\n",
    "    return circuit\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convolution circuit\n",
    "def U(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    # gate operations:\n",
    "    circuit.cnot(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.ry(symbols[0], q0)\n",
    "    circuit.ry(symbols[1], q1)\n",
    "    circuit.cnot(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.ry(symbols[2], q0)\n",
    "    circuit.ry(symbols[3], q1)\n",
    "    return circuit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "70480088-1dc3-4a41-9a5f-87f11f6672f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Convolution**"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m = (\n",
    "    Qfree([f\"q{i}\" for i in range(8)])\n",
    "    + (\n",
    "        Qconv(1, convolution_mapping=(U, 6))\n",
    "        + Qpool(filter=\"left\", pooling_mapping=(V, 1))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    * 3\n",
    ")\n",
    "circuit, symbols = convert_graph_to_circuit_qiskit(m)"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "36f659c8-5857-4b44-bfbf-18378b89ac6c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Cycle through unitary ansatzes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "f387216f-df07-45c7-b32e-c5df465fffde",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pooling circuit\n",
    "def V_1(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):  # 1\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.crx(symbols[0], q0, q1)\n",
    "    return circuit\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def V_2(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):  # 0\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.cnot(q0, q1)\n",
    "    return circuit\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convolution circuit\n",
    "def U_1(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):  # 1\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.crz(symbols[0], q0, q1)\n",
    "    return circuit\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def U_2(bits, symbols=None, circuit=None):  # 1\n",
    "    if type(bits[0]) == int:\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[0]}\"), QuantumRegister(1, f\"q{bits[1]}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Assume bits are strings and in the correct QASM format\n",
    "        q0, q1 = QuantumRegister(1, bits[0]), QuantumRegister(1, bits[1])\n",
    "    if circuit is None:\n",
    "        circuit = QuantumCircuit()\n",
    "        circuit.add_register(q0, q1)\n",
    "    circuit.cry(symbols[0], q0, q1)\n",
    "    return circuit\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "function_mappings = {\n",
    "    \"convolution\": [(U_1, 1), (U_2, 1)],\n",
    "    \"pooling\": [(V_1, 1), (V_2, 0)],\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "b14455f0-7b64-4b9f-a35b-314832982e95",
   "metadata": {},

     "data": {
